  "response": "I have identified the root cause of the inventory oversell defect and applied the correct check-before-decrement fix along with a regression test.\n\n### Root Cause\nIn `apps/synthetic-shop/src/inventory.rs`, the `reserve()` method decremented the available stock *before* checking if the requested quantity was actually available. This allowed stock to go negative (oversell) instead of failing gracefully.\n\n### Solution Applied\n1. **Check-before-decrement:** Modified `Inventory::reserve` to check if `qty > self.available` first. If true, it returns `Err(ReserveError::Insufficient { requested: qty, available: self.available })` and leaves the stock untouched.\n2. **Removed Dead Code Attribute:** Removed the `#[allow(dead_code)]` attribute from `ReserveError` as the `Insufficient` variant is now actively constructed.\n3. **Regression Tests:** Added a `tests` module containing `test_reserve_success` and `test_reserve_insufficient` to verify both code paths.\n4. **Validation:** Executed `cargo test`, `cargo clippy -- -D warnings`, and `cargo fmt --check` under `apps/synthetic-shop`, confirming all tests pass and standard checks are clean.",
